CHINA SUNSINE ‚Äì BENEIFICARY FROM HIGHER AUTO SALES IN CHINAFinancial PerformanceIn its 1st Half 2020 results  China Sunsine reported a revenue of RMB1.042b vs RMB1.413b with Net Profit coming in at RMB$80.2m down from RMB$266.6m a year ago due to the COVID19 Pandemic. Cash in Balance sheet total RMB$1.33b. Total Issue Shares stand at 972m with a market cap of SG$456m. Net Asset Value stands at RMB$2.66 or SGD$0.54.In its lastest update on 16 NOV 2020  Coy mentioned that 3Q 2020 reported record sales revenue of approximately RMB$600m  3Q utlisation rate stand at a high of 192 000 tons or 95% of capacity. 4Q 2020 would be higher than 3Q 2020 at a going rate of +10% for the month of October 2020. For Full Year Revenue could come in at RMB$2.24b++ ($0.6b+$0.66b(increment of 10%)+1stHalf $1.042b). China Sunsine would be logging its record FY2020 revenue and netprofit if it does do its neccesary cost managment as with 1st Half 2020.CatalystWe are seeing great interest in a push to accerelate the adoption of Electric Car(EVs) in China given tax savings. With a surging growth in China Electric Car such as the lights of NIO XiaoPeng Li Autos. The future look exciting for China Sunsine given its manfacturing rubber capabability.For 2021 China Sunsine would be looking at a production increase of 252 000 tons from 192 000 tons looking at a growth of 31%.
